  [Recent advancements in machine learning have shown that]
  Recent advancements in machine learning have shown that machine-learning can be used by individuals and communities to teach knowledge. A recent study published in the Journal of Computer Science has found a correlation between Machine Learning (MLT) performance (as well as machine language skills), but also a lack of understanding on the domain of computation/language research.
The focus for the paper is an overview of the topic, based on an analysis of 3D modeling which examined how MLM programs could be utilized to build complex models across multiple domains at different levels. The researchers also showed that the role of language skills (e.g., the ability to interpret questions in two languages without the need for a real language interpreter) was limited to learning about basic concepts such as mathematics, physics, astronomy, logic etc. This paper covers several areas of applied training including:
 Language Education; where information needs to be presented with the model; where relevant data can be read or written, and
