  [Once upon a time, there was a little girl]
  Once upon a time, there was a little girl in the garden and she had her head cut off by this beautiful young woman who seemed to be holding it down. It didn’t help that the girls were crying and there was nothing to look forward to seeing or talking about in the garden either.
It turns out that the girls, who are in their early stages of growth, aren’t really just the ones playing around with it. They are trying to get it right. This is what happened during one week of growing, when we got to see a few of them grow. We learned that they had been trying to make some flower arrangements for Christmas as well. The other three are in ‘a garden full of new stems’ but they didn’t give us much information on the actual roots. When I saw those, I knew that I wanted to know more about the growth process of these kinds of plants. One day we visited the nursery to look at my garden and they told me it had grown quite successfully without any problems. After three weeks of waiting for the root to have finished, we decided the best thing to do would be to visit my sister-in-law (who we now think is very kind) to get her started. She has given birth to one. And yes, she has made one. But since then we’ve been able to see what else she can come up with for our garden which includes a couple of different species that she will use in the next year. There are also several varieties that were planted that are growing this season but we still haven’t seen an end of the stem, so hopefully we won’t see any more.
